					</header><div class="entry-content clearfix">
						<p>From Mrs. Puller…</p>
<p>We have been working on fun and exciting ways to continue our After School Achievement Program with students. ASAP is launching a new Facebook Group. Students and their families can participate in many fun enrichment activities starting Monday. We will also have some activities for parents!  The program will run until May 15th.</p>
<p>Please go to West County ASAP Facebook page and join the group! Link – <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/526267488297371/?ref=group_header" rel="noopener" target="_blank">https://www.facebook.com/groups/526267488297371/?ref=group_header</a></p>
<p>Also, the District’s Remote Learning Resource website has a new ASAP at Home folder (<a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1ZxmOkP3YWkHGfLOcnVWhrf-s9Rw3t6eG?usp=sharing" rel="noopener" target="_blank">https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1ZxmOkP3YWkHGfLOcnVWhrf-s9Rw3t6eG?usp=sharing</a>). This contains activity calendars for each building. They will also be posted on the West County ASAP Facebook page.  </p>
<p>Students and parents who want to participate need to fill out the ASAP enrollment form located in the ASAP at Home folder. One must be filled out for each student and parent.</p>
<p>Some of the activities will provide supplies to a limited number of students, they can be delivered with the meals on Monday, picked up at the Elementary on Monday (for all sites) between 3-5:00 or even be delivered to your porch!  </p>
<p>More information is provided on the enrollment forms!</p>
<p>Hope you will participate in the new ASAP program! It will be a lot of fun!</p>
<hr style="width: 100%">
</div>
				

