							<div class="tg-one-half tg-one-half-last">
					<header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title">
							Learning Databases Now Available						</h2>
<!-- .entry-title -->
					</header><div class="entry-content clearfix">
						<p>We have been working with one of our educational resource vendors and they have opened up two of their main learning databases for our students to be able to use at home! Our teachers have been working on how to utilize these databases since last Friday.</p>
<p>The databases are called EBSCO &amp; LearningExpress and the login instructions can be found in our Remote Learning Resource Website (link – <a href="https://bit.ly/2xhbIAF" rel="noopener" target="_blank">https://bit.ly/2xhbIAF</a>). Parents &amp; students can feel free to use any of the resources you find on your own, or do the lessons &amp; activities your teachers share out. You can start using these databases today.<br>
*Please note that teachers will be sending out any resources or activities through our Remote Learning Resource Website.</p>
<p>Also note that any work completed using these databases is OPTIONAL and will not impact grades.</p>
<p>These databases do require internet access. We will always provide printed school-work packets that can be picked up. Contact your child’s teacher if you need a packet and they will work with our Central Office team to make sure that a packet is available for pick up.</p>
<p>The vendor has published several online tutorials on how to use the databases and you can access them here – <a href="https://search.more.net/node/30" rel="noopener" target="_blank">https://search.more.net/node/30</a></p>
<p>Go here (<a href="https://bit.ly/3bokFqM" rel="noopener" target="_blank">https://bit.ly/3bokFqM</a>) to see the login instructions.</p>
<hr style="width: 100%">
